.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jun 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-service-catalog - Browse and install services from the catalog


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel service catalog [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage the service catalog — a curated repository of containerized services
that can be installed on your Citadel node.

.PP
Run 'citadel service catalog update' to download or refresh the catalog,
then use list, search, and info to discover services.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for catalog


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-service(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-service-catalog-info(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-service-catalog-install(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-service-catalog-list(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-service-catalog-search(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-service-catalog-update(1)\fP
